evidence.text: MOTION FOR A PRELIMINARY INJUNCTION AND MEMORANDUM OF POINTS AND AUTHORITIES IN SUPPORT OF MOTION FOR A PRELIMINARY INJUNCTION

extracted.value: On March 21, 2025, Erie County, New York filed a Motion for a Preliminary Injunction (ECF No. 5) asking the court to order defendants to comply with grant requirements and to disburse funds immediately.

evidence.text: 2025-04-04 | Memorandum in opposition to re 5 Motion for Preliminary Injunction, filed by CORPORATION FOR NATIONAL AND COMMUNITY SERVICE, JENNIFER BASTRESS TAHMASEBI.

evidence.source_document: Defendants’ Opposition to Plaintiff’s Motion for Preliminary Injunction
evidence.text: Defendants’ Opposition to Plaintiff’s Motion for Preliminary Injunction

extracted.value: On April 4, 2025, the defendants—represented by Jennifer Bastress Tahmasebi of the Corporation for National and Community Service—filed an Opposition to the plaintiff’s Motion for Preliminary Injunction, asking the court to deny the motion and maintain the status quo.

evidence.text: Notice of Voluntary Dismissal ... Plaintiff Erie County New York hereby dismisses this case without prejudice, pursuant to Rule 41, because Defendant has changed its certification requirements since the filing of this suit. The motion for a preliminary injunction filed on March 21, 2025 (ECF No. 5), is accordingly withdrawn.

extracted.value: On April 14, 2025, Erie County, New York filed a Notice of Voluntary Dismissal, withdrawing the March 21, 2025 Motion for Preliminary Injunction and dismissing the case without prejudice.
